name: n,n'-dimethylacetamide
Reason: 1,1'-Dimethylacetamide has a melting point of around 30 degrees Celsius. The basic unit for this compound can be considered acetamide (with a melting point of -10.0°C) because the methyl groups significantly increase the melting point due to their ability to enhance π-π interactions and overall molecular rigidity. Each methyl group may contribute around +20 to +30°C.
